{"questionId":"13902725","questionHtml":"<p>If <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> adults in Melba are chosen independently and at random, find the probability that more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> of them have a weight greater than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>85</mn><mo> </mo><mi>kg</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> be the random variable the weight of an individual in the city of Melba)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi><mo>~</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>72</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>recognizing need to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>85</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(condone “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>86</mn></math>” for the <em><strong>M1</strong></em>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. correct sketch of normal curve&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0968</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0968005</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;seen</p>\n<p><br>let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Y</mi></math> be the random variable the number of people more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>85</mn><mo> </mo><mi>kg</mi></math></p>\n<p><br>attempt to use a binomial distribution&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Y</mi><mo>~</mo><mi mathvariant=\"norm